HIV/AIDS: Kasar Sin ta ba da rahoton karuwar masu cutar da kashi 14 cikin 100
Kasar Sin ta sanar da karuwar kaso 14 cikin 100 na mutanen da ke dauke da kwayar cutar HIV da AIDS.
A cikin ƙasar, fiye da mutane 820,000 ne suke fama da cutar, in ji hukumomin kiwon lafiya.
A cikin kwata na biyu na shekarar 2018 kadai, an samu kimanin mutane 40,000 da suka kamu da cutar.
A yawancin lokuta, ana samun sababbin cutar ta hanyar jima'i, wanda ya nuna cewa an canja yanayin da ake ciki a dā.
A dā, cutar HIV ta yadu da sauri a wasu ɓangarorin ƙasar Sin ta wurin ƙarin jini da aka yi daga jini.
Amma, adadin mutanen da suke samun cutar a wannan hanyar ya kusan zama sifili, kamar yadda jami'an kiwon lafiya na China suka faɗa a wani taro a lardin Yunnan.
Amma, idan aka kwatanta da shekarar da ta shige, adadin mutanen da suke da cutar kanjamau a China ya ƙaru da dubu ɗari.
Cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce ga al'ummar 'yan luwadi a China.
An haramta luwadi a China a 1997, amma nuna wariya ga LGBT jama'a ya kasance gama gari.
Domin ra'ayin ƙasar, bincike ya nuna cewa kashi 70 zuwa 90 bisa ɗari na maza da suke yin jima'i da maza za su auri mata.
Yawancin cututtukan da ake samu a cikin jima'i ana samun su ne daga rashin kāriya a jima'i.
Tun 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samar da maganin cutar a ko'ina a matsayin wani ɓangare na kokarin magance matsalar.
