Jakadan Amurka ya zargi China da "tsoratarwa" da "tallace-tallacen farfaganda"
Mako guda bayan da wata jaridar kasar Sin ta wallafa wata takarda mai shafi hudu a wata jaridar Amurka, tana mai nuna irin cinikin da ake yi tsakanin Amurka da Sin, jakadan Amurka a China ya zargi Beijing da amfani da kafafen yada labarai na Amurka wajen yada labaran karya.
Shugaban Amurka Donald Trump ya yi tsokaci a ranar Laraba kan wani sakon da aka wallafa a jaridar China Daily da ya bayyana a cikin jaridar Des Moines Register, jaridar da ta fi yawan talla a jihar Iowa, bayan da ya zargi China da neman tsoma baki a zaben da za a yi a ranar 6 ga watan Nuwamba, zargin da China ta musanta.
Zargin da Trump ya yi wa Beijing na kokarin tsoma baki a zaben Amurka ya nuna abin da jami'an Amurka suka fada wa Reuters cewa wani sabon mataki ne na kamfen da Washington ta kaddamar don matsa lamba kan China.
Duk da cewa ba a hana gwamnatocin kasashen waje tallata tallace-tallace don inganta kasuwancin su ba, Beijing da Washington a halin yanzu suna cikin yaƙin cinikayya mai tsanani kuma sun ɗora wa juna haraji da yawa kan shigo da kayayyaki.
China ta yi amfani da takunkumin da ta kafa a farkon yakin cinikayya don ta kara da masu fitar da kayayyaki zuwa jihohi kamar Iowa, wanda Jam'iyyar Republican ta Trump ta yi wa goyon baya, in ji masana na China da Amurka.
Terry Branstad, jakadan Amurka a China kuma tsohon gwamnan Iowa, jihar da ke da matukar muhimmanci wajen fitar da kayayyakin gona zuwa China, ya ce Beijing ta yi wa ma'aikatan Amurka, manoma da kamfanonin Amurka illa.
China, kamar yadda Branstad ya rubuta a cikin wata sanarwa a cikin jaridar Des Moines Register ta ranar Lahadi, "tana yin irin wannan barazanar ta hanyar buga tallace-tallace na farfaganda a cikin jaridunmu na 'yanci".
"A kokarin yada wannan farfaganda, gwamnatin China tana amfani da al'adun 'yancin fadin albarkacin baki da kuma' yancin 'yan jarida na Amurka, ta hanyar buga talla a cikin Des Moines Register", in ji Branstad.
"A bambance, a cikin dakunan Beijing, za ku sami muryoyi kaɗan da ba su da gaskiya kuma babu wakilcin gaskiya na ra'ayoyi daban-daban da jama'ar kasar Sin za su iya yi game da matsalar tattalin arzikin China, tunda kafofin watsa labarai suna ƙarƙashin ikon Jam'iyyar Kwaminis ta Sin", ya rubuta.
Ya kara da cewa "daya daga cikin manyan jaridu a China sun kauce wa tayin buga" labarinsa, ko da yake bai bayyana wanne ba.
